 {"id":"bd-2ej","title":"Implement ctx.call_tool() for cross-component access","description":"# Context: Call Tool from Handler

## Background
Python FastMCP allows calling tools from within other tool handlers via ctx.call_tool(). This enables tool composition, code reuse, and building higher-level abstractions from primitive tools.

## Requirements

### McpContext API
```rust
impl McpContext {
    /// Call another tool from within a handler
    ///
    /// This enables tool composition - building complex tools from simpler ones.
    ///
    /// # Example
    /// ```rust
    /// #[tool]
    /// async fn analyze_and_store(
    ///     ctx: &McpContext,
    ///     data: String,
    /// ) -> Result<String, ToolError> {
    ///     // Call analysis tool
    ///     let analysis = ctx.call_tool("analyze", json!({"input": data})).await?;
    ///
    ///     // Call storage tool with analysis result
    ///     let text = analysis.content[0].as_text().unwrap();
    ///     ctx.call_tool("store", json!({"data": text})).await?;
    ///
    ///     Ok("Analysis complete and stored".into())
    /// }
    /// ```
    pub async fn call_tool(&self, name: &str, args: Value) -> McpResult<CallToolResult>

    /// Call a tool and extract text result
    pub async fn call_tool_text(&self, name: &str, args: Value) -> McpResult<String>

    /// Call a tool and parse JSON result
    pub async fn call_tool_json<T: DeserializeOwned>(
        &self,
        name: &str,
        args: Value,
    ) -> McpResult<T>
}
```

### Recursion Protection
```rust
const MAX_TOOL_CALL_DEPTH: u32 = 10;

pub struct McpContextInner {
    // ... existing fields ...
    tool_call_depth: u32,
}

impl McpContext {
    pub async fn call_tool(&self, name: &str, args: Value) -> McpResult<CallToolResult> {
        // Check recursion depth
        if self.inner.tool_call_depth >= MAX_TOOL_CALL_DEPTH {
            return Err(McpError::internal(format!(
                "Maximum tool call depth ({}) exceeded - possible infinite recursion",
                MAX_TOOL_CALL_DEPTH
            )));
        }

        let router = self.inner.router.as_ref()
            .ok_or_else(|| McpError::internal("No router available in context"))?;

        // Create child context with incremented depth
        let child_ctx = self.with_incremented_tool_depth();

        // Find and call tool handler
        router.call_tool(&child_ctx, name, args).await
    }
}
```

### Same Tool Recursion
Allow controlled self-recursion (e.g., recursive algorithms) but enforce depth limit:

```rust
#[tool]
async fn factorial(ctx: &McpContext, n: u64) -> Result<u64, ToolError> {
    if n <= 1 {
        return Ok(1);
    }
    let sub = ctx.call_tool_json::<u64>("factorial", json!({"n": n - 1})).await?;
    Ok(n * sub)
}
```

## Files to Modify
- crates/fastmcp-core/src/context.rs
- crates/fastmcp-server/src/handler.rs
- crates/fastmcp-server/src/router.rs

## User Experience Considerations
- Clear error messages for recursion limit
- Show call stack in error when depth exceeded
- Progress token forwarding for nested calls
